#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
GOGLib — managed GOG library archival.

Cross-platform Python tool that wraps a backend downloader (lgogdownloader on
Linux/macOS, gogrepoc on Windows) and adds: manifest-tracked downloads so files
can be moved off-disk without triggering redownloads, segmented batches by
first letter, automatic franchise-based folder organization, OST format
priority filtering, version archiving, and interactive language-extras audit.

Subcommands:
  refresh                              Refresh backend cache + dump library JSON
  plan [--letter X] [--game R]         Show what would be downloaded
  sync [--letter X] [--game R]         Download new files and organize
  process [--letter X] [--game R]      Re-run post-processing on existing
                                       staging without re-downloading
  audit [--review-all]                 Interactively review extras matching
                                       suspicious language tokens
  reorganize [--dry-run]               Move files to match current config
  forget --letter X|--game R [--yes]   Remove matching entries from manifest
  status                               Manifest summary
  config [--write-default]             Show / initialize config

Letter values:  num | all | a-z | a-c (range)

Files (per-OS):
  Linux/macOS:
    ~/.config/goglib/config.json
    ~/.config/goglib/franchises.json
    ~/.local/share/goglib/manifest.json
    ~/.local/share/goglib/library.json
  Windows:
    %APPDATA%\\goglib\\config.json
    %APPDATA%\\goglib\\franchises.json
    %APPDATA%\\goglib\\manifest.json
    %APPDATA%\\goglib\\library.json
"""

